Wrong. Education refers to the place of the individual's formative education, not the degree they graduated with. To add this, it can be placed in parentheses with the year of graduation after the relevant institution, i.e. Christ Church, Oxford (BA 1928). On a side note, the Oxford MA is awarded by right upon application 21 terms following matriculation and does not require further study so cannot be awarded in a class or specific subject: MA English Language & Literature is incorrect.
